         Hit % is calculated based on level and ATK...we know our pet's levels so it would be nice to know their ATK unbuffed (we can do the math to get the ATK of a buffed pet).</P><P>Lvl 60 tanks get ATK 1300 and higher with average stats and gear. Compared to our pets, when fighting a mob of say level 45 a tank hits between 60% and 75% of the time, our pets hit roughly 55% of the time. Our pets still outdamage most tanks but the reason here lies in the fact that pets have a low dmg cap (the lvl 49 necro pet can't hit for less than 15 unless it's a miss) whilst a melee can git for just 1 point of damage.</P><P>Highest mob I've soloed was an Elder Wyvern in SF. The mob is pretty high level and I noticed that my pet (rogue pet) hit a lot less than against even Mature Wyverns (level difference about 1 to 3 levels I think) - hit rate was roughly 45% I think, mob snared/feared all the time, and against lower mobs hit rate gets as high as 55% for XP mobs (I have other hits in a seperate window and often stand close enough to get all/most hit msgs - I have other misses off). The higher HP on the mob was dealt with through 2 splurts and 2 BoD which both did full dmg (4700dmg total) added with several negligeable dooming darknesses.</P><P>This means that a slight increase in levels of a mob results in a pet losing masses of it's effectiveness...</P><P>BTW to compare:</P><P>-My lvl 60 cleric with epic and pretty low STR (tad over 100) has an ATK of about 800 and hits up to 40% of the time on regular mobs</P><P>-My rogue pet has about the same hit rate against similliar mobs...it is however lower level so I assume it has higher ATK...how much higher a fanatic tank needs to tell as I have not tested the effect of buffs like CoP on hit rate</P><P><BR>Sumeine highsoul<BR>High Priestess of Tunare<BR>Bertoxx</P><P>Vilye D'Revenn<BR>Defiler of Bertoxxulous<BR>Bertoxx</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of P